{"id":"2011.12260","submitter":"Imene Trigui","authors":"Imene Trigui, Wessam Ajib, Wei-Ping Zhu, and Marco Di Renzo","title":"Performance Evaluation and Diversity Analysis of RIS-Assisted\n  Communications Over Generalized Fading Channels in the Presence of Phase\n  Noise","comments":null,"journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"cs.IT math.IT","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  In this paper, we develop a comprehensive theoretical framework for analyzing\nthe performance of reconfigurable intelligent surfaces (RISs)-assisted\ncommunication systems over generalized fading channels and in the presence of\nphase noise. To this end, we propose the Fox's H model as a unified fading\ndistribution for a large number of widely used generalized fading channels. In\nparticular, we derive a unified analytical framework for computing the outage\nprobability and for estimating the achievable diversity order of RIS-aided\nsystems in the presence of phase shifts that either are optimally configured or\nare impaired by phase noise. The resulting expressions are general, as they\nhold for an arbitrary number of reflecting elements, and various channel fading\nand phase noise distributions. As far as the diversity order is concerned,\nnotably, we introduce an asymptotic analytical framework for determining the\ndiversity order in the absence of phase noise, as well as sufficient conditions\nbased on upper bounds and lower bounds for ensuring that RIS-assisted systems\nachieve the full diversity order in the presence of phase noise. More\nspecifically, if the absolute difference between pairs of phase errors is less\nthan $\\pi/2$, RIS-assisted communications achieve the full diversity order over\nindependent fading channels, even in the presence of phase noise. The\ntheoretical frameworks and findings are validated with the aid of Monte Carlo\nsimulations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 24 Nov 2020 18:16:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-11-25"}
